description:
Reporting to the Associate Director of Student Development Services (Counselling), the Student Care Advisor will be responsible to:

* Manage referrals of cases from CityUHK academic or administrative departments and external agencies, including government anti-scam agencies;

* Provide confidential, one-to-one pastoral care, empathetic support, and practical advice to student victims;

* Conduct comprehensive needs and risk assessments;

* Clearly explain students‚Äô options regarding university procedures (e.g. reporting to the university) and external avenues (e.g., reporting to police, accessing specialist charities);

* Develop and implement personalised support plans to help students regain a sense of control and safety;

* Act as a central referral point to other internal services (counselling, academic support, student residence, financial aid, security and safety) and external agencies (rape crisis centers, scam victim support);

* Maintain accurate and confidential case records;

* Work closely with the SDS Counselling Service team and other university departments to ensure a seamless support network for students; and

* Perform any other duties as assigned.

The appointee will be required to work flexible hours, including evenings and weekends as required.

### **Requirements**

* A Bachelor‚Äôs degree in Social Work/Counselling/Counselling Psychology, or a related field with at least 10 years of relevant experience; or a Master‚Äôs degree in a related field with at least 5 years of relevant experience;

* Demonstrate maturity in handling various student crisis situations;

* Communicate effectively both verbally and in writing, including proficient telephone skills;

* Ability to handle challenging and emotionally charged situations with sensitivity, empathy, and self-control;

* Computer literate with strong typing skills;

* Familiarity with relevant local agencies and resources, including social services, law enforcement, and legal support;

* Understand the importance of confidentiality and safe working practices;

* Appreciate diversity issues and principles; and

* Comprehend the impact of critical events on students.

Shortlisted candidates will be invited for a written test.

### **Salary and Conditions of Service**

Remuneration package will be highly competitive, commensurate with qualifications and experience. Appointment will be made on a fixed-term contract; fringe benefits include gratuity, leave, medical and dental schemes.

### **Information and Application**

Further information on the post and the University is available at http://www.cityu.edu.hk, or from the Human Resources Office, City University of Hong Kong, Tat Chee Avenue, Kowloon Tong, Hong Kong [Email : hrojob@cityu.edu.hk/Fax : 2788 1154 or 3442 0311].

To apply, please submit an online application. The closing date is **13 February 2026**. Applications will receive full consideration and only shortlisted applicants will be contacted. The University‚Äôs privacy policy is available on the homepage.

*City University of Hong Kong is an equal opportunity employer. We are committed to the principle of diversity. Personal data provided by applicants will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purposes.*

